dfischer.utils

Class ThreadSaveLogVector

  • java.lang.Object
    • dfischer.utils.ThreadSaveLogVector
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    LogVectorInterface

    public class ThreadSaveLogVector
extends java.lang.Object
implements LogVectorInterface
    Collect log output of multiple threads and dump it later in a safe way.
    Please note that the thread safety must be enabled first by calling enableSpinLock(true).
    See Also:
    enableSpinLock(boolean), LogVectorInterface, LogVector

    • Method Detail

      • enableSpinLock

        public void enableSpinLock(boolean doEnable)
        Enable or disable thread save synchronisation for all methods (default: disabled). Note 1: thread save synchronisation is normally not needed because this class uses already java.util.Vector. Note 2: this method can be called at any time. Also multiple calls of this method are supported.
        Parameters:
        doEnable - true = enable thread save synchronisation, false = disable thread save synchronisation
